            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EAre%20you%20going%20through%20a%20severe%20trial%20today%3F%20If%20so%2C%20your%20mind%20must%20settle%20certain%20issues.%20First%2C%20your%20reaction%20to%20the%20trial%20should%20be%20one%20of%20joy%2C%20for%20the%20testing%20of%20your%20faith%20develops%20perseverance%20(James%201%3A2-3).%20Rejoice%20when%20trials%20come%20your%20way%2C%20because%20without%20a%20test%2C%20there%20can%20be%20no%20testimony.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESecond%2C%20you%20should%20remember%20that%20if%20you%20persevere%20and%20withstand%20the%20test%2C%20you%20will%20receive%20the%20crown%20of%20life%20(v.%2012).%20All%20your%20earthly%20difficulties%20are%20simply%20adding%20jewels%20to%20your%20eternal%20crown%20and%20reward.%20That%20is%20a%20life-changing%20way%20to%20look%20at%20trials%2C%20now%20isn't%20it%3F%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EFinally%2C%20you%20should%20never%20blame%20God%20for%20all%20your%20trials.%20He%20does%20not%20tempt%20you%20to%20sin%20and%20only%20gives%20you%20what%20is%20good.%20%22Whatever%20is%20good%20and%20perfect%20comes%20to%20us%20from%20God%20above%2C%20who%20created%20all%20heaven's%20lights%22%20(v.%2017).%20Always%20remember%20%22how%20kind%20the%20Lord%20is!%20How%20good%20he%20is!%20So%20merciful%2C%20this%20God%20of%20ours!%22%20(Psalm%20116%3A5).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20summary%20of%20the%20matter%3F%20Trials%20are%20working%20in%20your%20character%2C%20they%20are%20temporary%2C%20and%20God%20is%20concerned%20about%20your%20trials.%20One%20day%20you%20will%20be%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20trial%2C%20saying%20to%20yourself%20as%20the%20psalmist%20said%2C%20%22Now%20I%20can%20rest%20again%2C%20for%20the%20Lord%20has%20been%20so%20good%20to%20me%22%20(Psalm%20116%3A7).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
